I would never order from this place ever again. Not only they messed up our order, they sent us possibly expired food. Their operation is extremely slopy and possibly not sanitary.  My fiance and I made a pick up order here. I arrived 20 mins later and my food was ready to be picked up on their table. But all the servers were just busy taking new orders on the phone and made at least 4 groups of people and their food waiting in line. After about 10 mins, I reached out to the server directly and made them package my food before they become completely cold.  The server seemed like she was rushing packaging my order. Putting things in and out of the bags constantly like she doesn't know what she is doing. So I asked straight to her face, "did you put tortillas in there?" She looked and me and said "yes."  I arrived home with our food and surprise, not only there were no tortillas, they completely forgot to put our dessert which we already paid for. So my fiance called again. They made us pick up flan and tortillas in person, so I went. We even ordered additional dessert on top of it.  I came back home the second time with my orders. My fiance took her first bite of the flan and she immediately spits it out and head to the bathroom. She said her flan didn't taste right at all. I smelled it and it smelled like some sort of tap water and heavy scent of refrigerator was coming from the flan itself. This flan smelled like it has been sitting in the refrigerator for weeks, possibly months. Doesn't have any individual expiration date marked on it to verify if it's safe to eat. And of course, no tortillas were included again.  I am extremely disappointed. It seems like they just don't care at all. They constantly messed up our orders and even gave us questionable food that  made my fiance throw up. This is possibly one of the worst dining experiences in this year.  Would not recommend this place at all.

This is a gem of taco spot in the heights.  Small,  clean (So important), economical, and actually run by people who likely eat tacos themselves.  You'd be surprised how many restaurant workers don't like the food they sell.  Lol.  These tacos are authentic,  service is good and they deliver! Standout dishes are the guacamole and the fish tacos.  Fantastico! Very nice horchata and cinnamon hot chocolate too.

This taco place just opened up not long ago and I have been living around this neighborhood for over 2 years now so I know every single joint around here and trust me I can count the good places with 1 hand only but finally, about time this food is amazing. Everything is made fresh even the tortillas for the tacos, you cant get any fresher than that. So far I have tried almost the entire menu. I prefer ordering deliveries, not sure how they do it but food is always delivered before 25 minutes which is amazing considering the other places thru Seamless that take about 1 hour to send your cold food and they still get upset when you tell them. Anyways this place is great, the owner is this lady who has been cooking her entired life and has owned a few spots before so she knows what she is doing. The place is small but cozy and inviting. Not sure you would grab a table but try, maybe if you are lucky but if you do you will be very happy eating on this bright colorful tables and chairs. Try the enchiladas  Suizas green sauce with Chicken or my fav al pastor 😋 Mole enchiladas is another great choice. The soups you gotta try the Chicken or pozole soups with tostadas and chopped onions, cilantro and sliced radish. All tacos are great here and orders are pretty generous so I am sure you will be set for the whole day. Oh and the wait staff is great and knowledgeable, sometimes I think they know what I wanna eat. Trust me no other places serves food like them and I have congratulated them many times cause I am glad to spend my money for something I can finally enjoy.
